As I move into ICT4D, I find myself holding this tension. I value well-designed systems, but I am\
learning that technology must remain embedded in context. Perhaps what development requires\
is not less technology, but greater technical humility. Treating tools as instruments within social\
ecosystems rather than as standalone solutions. Machinery may organize delivery, but its\
purpose must remain human flourishing, not mechanical efficiency.}
